  "notes": "Khasi (Meghalaya, India). Austroasiatic, Mon-Khmer branch — unrelated to IA, Dravidian, or Munda. One of only two scheduled languages not from IA or Dravidian families. Written in Latin script since Welsh/British missionary period (1840s). Matrilineal society; shares phonological typology with Southeast Asian Mon-Khmer.",
